## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   date = col_double(),

##    = col_double(),
##   _ = col_double(),

Prices$date <- Prices %>% with(ifelse(nchar(Prices$date)==6,paste0(date,"0.01"),paste0(date,".01")))
Prices$date <- gsub("-","",as.Date(Prices$date,"%Y.%m.%d"))
## Warning in strptime(x, format, tz = "GMT"): unknown timezone 'zone/tz/
## 2017c.1.0/zoneinfo/Asia/Seoul'

Prices$__up <- c(1,diff(Prices$_))/Prices$_

weather <- read_csv("../data_need/weather_.csv")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   date = col_integer(),
##   weather_str = col_character(),
##   min_Temperature = col_double(),
##   max_Temperature = col_double(),
##   Precipitation = col_double(),
##   snow = col_double()
## )
weather <- weather %>% subset(date <= 20171212)
weather$check <- ifelse(weather$date %in% rec$date[rec$date>=20160101],weather$date,0)

for (i in nrow(weather):1){
  temp <- ifelse(weather$check[i]!=0,weather$check[i],temp)
  weather$check[i] <- ifelse(weather$check[i]==0,temp,weather$check[i])
}

temp <- weather %>% mutate(index=1) %>% dcast(check ~ weather_str,value.var="index")
## Aggregation function missing: defaulting to length
colnames(temp)[1] <- "date"
temp1 <- weather %>% group_by(check) %>% select(-weather_str,-date) %>% summarise_all(funs(sum = sum))
colnames(temp1)[1] <- "date"
temp <- temp %>% left_join(temp1)
## Joining, by = "date"
weather_temp <- temp

3.KNN

total_train <- total_train %>% select(-pred)
total_test <- total_test %>% select(-pred)

knn.fit_train<-kknn(price ~ ., train = total_train %>% select(-date), test = total_train)
knn.fit_test<-kknn(price ~ ., train = total_train %>% select(-date), test = total_test)

total_train$pred <- fitted(knn.fit_train)
total_test$pred <- fitted(knn.fit_test)

total_s <- total_train %>% bind_rows(total_test)
total_s %>% select(date,price,pred) %>% ggplot(aes(x=ymd(date),y=price))+
  geom_point(color="black") + geom_point(aes(y=pred),color="red") + geom_vline(xintercept = ymd(20170530))

sqrt(mean((total_train$pred - total_train$price)^2))
## [1] 7470.672

## [1] 6087.116

4. Neuralnet

total_train <- total_train %>% select(-pred)
total_test <- total_test %>% select(-pred)

INPUT_NODES<-10
HIDDEN_NODES<-INPUT_NODES*2
OUTPUT_NODES<-5
ITERATION<-100

nnet_md<-nnet(formula = price~. ,data= total_train %>% select(-date),size=5,linout = TRUE,rang = 0.1,skip=TRUE,maxit = ITERATION)
## # weights:  197

5. Boosting

total_train <- total_train %>% select(-pred)
total_test <- total_test %>% select(-pred)

boosting <- gbm(price~., data = total_train %>% select(-date),
                distribution = "gaussian",
                n.trees = 10000)
## Warning in gbm.fit(x, y, offset = offset, distribution = distribution, w =
## w, : variable 1: energy_sun has no variation.
## Warning in gbm.fit(x, y, offset = offset, distribution = distribution, w =
## w, : variable 2: energy_general has no variation.
#
total_train$pred<-predict(boosting,total_train,n.trees=10000)
total_test$pred<-predict(boosting,total_test,n.trees=10000)

total_s <- total_train %>% bind_rows(total_test)
total_s %>% select(date,price,pred) %>% ggplot(aes(x=ymd(date),y=price))+
  geom_point(color="black") + geom_point(aes(y=pred),color="red") + geom_vline(xintercept = ymd(20170530))

sqrt(mean((total_train$pred - total_train$price)^2))
## [1] 9288.849
sqrt(mean((total_test$pred - total_test$price)^2))
## [1] 11712.47
